            <thetext>The css files should be revised and adapted to resolution independent css for

* Font-Size
* Images
* Height / Width of Widgets

body should have font-size 100% (depending on resolution). For all other classes em sizes should be used.

global: 100% EM: 1.0   16pt = 12px = 1em

See the following nice articles for this topic:

http://kyleschaeffer.com/best-practices/css-font-size-em-vs-px-vs-pt-vs/

http://www.sencha.com/blog/resolution-independent-mobile-ui

http://ajaxian.com/archives/the-death-of-the-pixel-as-we-know-it-the-new-dpi-web

http://blog.iwalt.com/2010/06/targeting-the-iphone-4-retina-display-with-css3-media-queries.html

http://www.cloudfour.com/css-media-query-for-mobile-is-fools-gold/</thetext>
